OL,6,FAsked if he was in a state of shock,
OL,7,Fhe responded: "It is very hard to take
OL,8,Fin initially for the first 30 seconds
OL,9,Fto one minute, you're just standing
OL,10,Fthere in disbelief.
OL,12,F"But then you have to switch off as a
OL,13,Fperson and you have to remember that
OL,14,Fyou're in charge and you've got to
OL,15,Fdeal with it."
OL,17,FHe added: "I didn't want to be there,
OL,18,Fabsolutely. I wanted to run ` but I
OL,19,Fhad to do my job."
