OL,6,FMr Baxter was the RUC sub-divisional
OL,7,Fcommander in Omagh on the day of the
OL,8,Fblast.
OL,10,FHe told how he was off-duty when he
OL,11,Freceived a call that there had been a
OL,12,Fbomb warning. The warning incorrectly
OL,13,Fstated the bomb was close to the
OL,14,Fcourthouse and many people were
OL,15,Fevacuated in the direction of Market
OL,16,FStreet.
OL,18,FSoon after, he said he heard on the
OL,19,Fnews that a bomb had exploded and
OL,20,Fheaded to the town's RUC station to
OL,21,Fassume command of the police operation.
